      "## Who Should Use FTWZ? Industry Applications",
      "FTWZs are particularly beneficial for several categories of businesses. Bulk commodity importers who need flexible, long-term storage for raw materials benefit from the unlimited storage duration. Trading companies managing multi-country distribution networks can leverage the re-export flexibility to serve regional markets efficiently. Pharmaceutical companies requiring GDP-compliant cold storage find FTWZ facilities offer the temperature-controlled infrastructure they need. Electronics importers managing Just-In-Time (JIT) inventory can stage products in the FTWZ and release them precisely when needed. E-commerce companies looking to optimise cross-border fulfillment can use FTWZs as bonded fulfillment centres. Automotive companies importing CKD/SKD kits can store components duty-free until assembly schedules require them.",
      "The growth of India's FTWZ sector is closely tied to government initiatives like 'Make in India,' 'Atmanirbhar Bharat,' and the National Logistics Policy, which prioritise trade facilitation and logistics cost reduction. The government's target is to reduce logistics costs from the current 14% of GDP to under 10%, and FTWZs play a critical role in achieving this objective by reducing duty-related capital costs and improving supply chain efficiency.",
      "## FTWZ and E-Commerce: The Cross-Border Fulfillment Opportunity",
      "One of the fastest-growing applications of FTWZ infrastructure is cross-border e-commerce fulfillment. As Indian consumers increasingly purchase directly from international brands and marketplaces, the demand for efficient cross-border logistics has surged. FTWZs offer a compelling solution for e-commerce companies looking to pre-position international inventory close to the Indian market without committing to customs duty until individual orders are placed.",
      "In this model, international sellers ship bulk inventory to an Indian FTWZ, where goods are stored duty-free. When an Indian customer places an order, the specific item is cleared from the FTWZ (with duty and IGST paid on that single unit or small batch), and dispatched for last-mile delivery. This pre-positioning model eliminates the 7-15 day international shipping wait that typically deters Indian consumers from cross-border purchases, while the FTWZ's duty deferment benefit means the seller doesn't need to pay duties on unsold inventory.",
