      "## FTWZ vs Bonded Warehouse vs CFS: Key Differences",
      "Understanding the differences between FTWZs, regular bonded warehouses, and Container Freight Stations (CFS) is essential for making informed logistics decisions. Bonded warehouses allow duty deferment but have limitations on storage duration (typically 1-3 years with extensions), do not allow trading within the zone, and offer limited value-addition capabilities. CFS facilities are primarily designed for customs clearance and short-term storage, with limited warehousing capacity and no duty deferment benefits beyond the initial free period.",
      "FTWZs, by contrast, offer unlimited storage duration, permit international trading within the zone, allow value-addition activities, and provide the full suite of duty and tax deferment benefits. The infrastructure is purpose-built to international standards with modern warehouse management systems, CCTV surveillance, fire safety systems, and 24/7 security — making them the premium choice for serious importers and trading houses.",
      "## Getting Started with FTWZ: Implementation Guide",
